properties.headline: Winter Weather Advisory issued January 10 at 3:16PM CST until January 12 at 6:00AM CST by NWS Green Bay WI
properties.description:
...WINTER WEATHER WILL IMPACT TRAVEL THIS WEEKEND...

.Two rounds of winter weather will impact the region tonight
through Saturday night. The first round will bring 1 to 3 inches
of snow to the Fox Valley and lakeshore counties tonight, along
with blowing and drifting snow. The second round will arrive late
Saturday afternoon and early evening, and bring 3 to 7 inches of
snow, and considerable blowing and drifting snow, to much of
central, northeast and east central Wisconsin. The worst conditions
will occur in the Fox Valley and lakeshore areas, where the
highest snowfall totals are expected, and northeast winds will
gust to 35 to 40 mph. Travel conditions will be significantly
impacted.

The strong northeast winds will also result in increased
potential for lakeshore flooding, shoreline erosion, and ice
shoves on the bay and Lake Winnebago.

* WHAT...Snow expected. Total snow accumulations of 2 to 5 inches.
Winds gusting to 25 to 30 mph, causing areas of blowing and
drifting snow in open areas.

* WHERE...Waupaca and Waushara Counties.

* WHEN...From 3 PM Saturday to 6 AM CST Sunday.

* IMPACTS...Plan on slippery road conditions. Areas of blowing
snow could significantly reduce visibility.
properties.instruction:
Slow down and use caution while traveling.

The latest road conditions for the state you are calling from can
be obtained by calling 5 1 1.

NWSheadline: WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY IN EFFECT FROM 3 PM SATURDAY TO 6 AM CST SUNDAY
